9. How many Austraits contributors are from Australian institutions?

```{r}

austraits$contributors %>% filter(grepl('Australia', affiliation)) %>% nrow


```

Answer: 491 (out of 606)

Note: In this and other cases, you can't simply filter directly on "austraits$contributors$affiliation" -- this object would be of character type, basically a long sequence of character "strings", and what we want is a structured dataframe or tibble like what you are familiar with, with rows and columns that can be filtered and selected for easily using dplyr functions


